xxl.core.indexStructures

Class MVBTree.Lifespan

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.indexStructures.Separator
      • xxl.core.indexStructures.BPlusTree.KeyRange
        • xxl.core.indexStructures.MVBTree.Lifespan
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Comparable, Descriptor
    Enclosing class:
    MVBTree

    public static class MVBTree.Lifespan
extends BPlusTree.KeyRange
    Objects of this class are version intervals and represent life spans of the entries sotred in the MVBTree. A Lifespan consists of a begin and end versions and has one the following forms:
    • [beginVersion, null[ the entry became valid startig from beginVersion and it is still alive.
    • [beginVersion, endVersion[ the entry became valid startig from beginVersion and it was deleted at endVersion.
    • [beginVersion, endVersion] this form is used to express query or root regions.
    Version:
    Aug 19, 2003
